<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="372" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,690,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,834,859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The fore femur only with a subapical indentation and a small single apical tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1290,1377,834,859]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[1346,1377,835,859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); the unmodified inner surface of the fore tibiae (
<figureCitation box="[681,771,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[739,771,871,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); the relatively large male abdominal segment VIII and pygophore (
<figureCitation box="[289,432,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 48, 53</figureCitation>
); the proctiger laterally raised and with a pair of blackish dots (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1269,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[1238,1269,906,931]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
); the typically triangular shape of the paramere blade (
<figureCitation box="[612,709,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[723,754,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">83</figureCitation>
); accessory lateral sclerites of endosoma relatively thick in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[302,399,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 71" captionStartId="8.[151,264,774,796]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,209,747]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[204,1384,193,752]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 71. Endosoma of Metrocoris spp. (males) in dorsal view. 67. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 68. M. astictus sp. nov.; 69. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 70. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 71. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 71</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[414,445,979,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">81</figureCitation>
); female abdominal sternum VII laterally constricted, apical half forming a relatively broad lobe, caudal margin without median notch (Fig. 
<number box="[762,793,1015,1039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="38.0">38</number>
), are the diagnostic features of 
<taxonomicName box="[1143,1253,1014,1038]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1143,1253,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">M. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1260,1350,1014,1039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1260,1350,1014,1039]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="373" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,690,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,527,1050,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Description. Apterous male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[542,636,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 20" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1737,1759]" captionTargetBox="[225,1362,417,1701]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[209,1378,409,1716]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 20. Habitus of Metrocoris spp. (apterous males). 13 – 16. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (13: Qingchen mountain; 14: Laojun mountain; 15: Xinmin village; 16: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 17. M. astictus sp. nov.; 18. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 19. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 20. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 2.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269715/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 20</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[649,681,1051,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 21 – 28" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1775,1797]" captionTargetBox="[196,1386,524,1745]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[184,1403,517,1753]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 21 – 28. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (males). 21 – 24. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (21: Qingchen mountain; 22: Laojun mountain; 23: Xinmin village; 24: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 25. M. astictus sp. nov.; 26. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 27. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 28. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269716/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">28</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<number box="[846,962,1050,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="6.665" valueMax="6.71" valueMin="6.62">6.62–6.71</number>
, body width (across acetabula) 
<number box="[1317,1432,1051,1075]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="3.145" valueMax="3.21" valueMin="3.08">3.08–3.21</number>
. Colour: dorsal yellow with prominent black stripes; interocular dark mark usually arrowhead shaped, bifid posteriorly, along inner margin of eyes without narrow dark line; first antennal segment yellowish brown, remaining segments usually blackish; rostrum yellowish with black apex; pronotum with T-shaped black stripe, lateral pronotal stripe very broad; mesonotum with median slender longitudinally stripe, sublateral stripes broader than lateral stripes, nearly equal in width to transverse bands; longitudinal dark stripe of mesopleuron slender, running about 
<number box="[313,323,1267,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[334,350,1267,1291]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="2.0">2</number>
of its length, very close to anterior margin but far from short acetabular mark; anterior transverse stripe of metanotum laterally confluent with posterior stripe of metanotum; fore femora with apical dark ring and four longitudinal marks, ventral mark connected with ring, remaining marks not confluent, inner mark relatively pale and bright, external mark broad and blackish brown; middle and hind femora yellowish, tibiae and tarsi black; abdomen mainly blackish dorsally, abdominal tergites II–IV blackish, abdominal tergites V–VII blackish anteriorly and yellowish posteriorly; abdominal segment VIII with a large rectangular blackish mark in dorsal view, posteriorly with moderately bifid-shaped. Genital segments yellowish. Structural characters: head length 
<number pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.53" valueMax="0.55" valueMin="0.51">0.51– 0.55</number>
, head width 
<number box="[356,470,1518,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.65" valueMax="1.69" valueMin="1.61">1.61–1.69</number>
, minimum interocular width 
<number box="[813,929,1518,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.685" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.67">0.67–0.70</number>
; antenna about 
<number box="[1115,1164,1519,1543]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.9">0.90</number>
times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments I–IV: 
<number box="[552,604,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="2.71">2.71</number>
, 
<number box="[616,668,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.4">1.40</number>
, 
<number box="[680,731,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.18">1.18</number>
, 
<number box="[744,796,1555,1579]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.7">0.70</number>
; pronotum slightly narrower than head, pronotum length 
<number box="[151,265,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.6799999999999999" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.66">0.66–0.70</number>
, pronotum width 
<number box="[471,586,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.885" valueMax="1.9" valueMin="1.87">1.87–1.90</number>
; fore femora moderately incrassate (
<figureCitation box="[1007,1093,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[1062,1093,1591,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
), ratio length/width 
<number box="[1327,1364,1590,1615]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="4.5">4.5</number>
, inner side not modified, with a subapical indentation, and a small single apical tooth; inner surface of fore tibiae not modified (
<figureCitation box="[270,357,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 39 – 43" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1943,1965]" captionTargetBox="[178,1406,1766,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[173,1413,1764,1921]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 39 – 43. Line drawings of fore legs of Metrocoris spp. (males) in lateral view. 39. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 40. M. astictus sp. nov.; 41. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 42. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 43. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 cm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269718/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[325,357,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="43.0">43</number>
</figureCitation>
); lengths of leg segments (femur, tibia and tarsus): fore leg: 
<number box="[1063,1115,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="3.12">3.12</number>
, 
<number box="[1129,1178,1662,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="2.52">2.52</number>
and 
<number box="[1238,1287,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.01">1.01</number>
(
<number box="[1305,1358,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.1">0.10</number>
+ 
<number box="[1373,1423,1663,1687]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.91">0.91</number>
), middle leg: 
<number box="[284,335,1699,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="8.21">8.21</number>
, 
<number box="[347,395,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="6.11">6.11</number>
and 
<number box="[448,497,1699,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="3.01">3.01</number>
(
<number box="[512,564,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="2.62">2.62</number>
+ 
<number box="[580,632,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.39">0.39</number>
), hind leg: 
<number box="[755,807,1699,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="8.02">8.02</number>
, 
<number box="[818,867,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="6.23">6.23</number>
and 
<number box="[921,970,1699,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.02">1.02</number>
(
<number box="[985,1037,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.52">0.52</number>
+ 
<number box="[1053,1105,1698,1723]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="0.5">0.50</number>
); dorsum of abdomen clothed with short shiny golden hair, venter of abdomen densely clothed with pale yellow hairs. Male terminalia: abdominal segment VIII more or less rectangle (
<figureCitation box="[692,775,1770,1795]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[744,775,1771,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
), relatively large, length 
<number box="[1054,1105,1770,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.58">1.58</number>
, width 
<number box="[1188,1239,1771,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.08">1.08</number>
, about 
<number box="[1320,1369,1770,1795]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="1.46">1.46</number>
times as long as wide, posterior margin with dense brown erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[879,964,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[932,964,1807,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
); pygophore subovate (
<figureCitation box="[1229,1313,1806,1831]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[1282,1313,1806,1831]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
), proctiger laterally raised and with a pair of blackish dots (
<figureCitation box="[702,786,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 44 – 58" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1297,1319]" captionTargetBox="[184,1395,207,1269]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[164,1424,193,1276]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 44 – 58. Photographs of abdominal segment VIII, pygophore and proctiger of Metrocoris spp. (males). 44, 49, 54. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 45, 50, 55. M. astictus sp. nov.; 46, 51, 56. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 47, 52, 57. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 48, 53, 58. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.4 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269719/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[755,786,1842,1867]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="58.0">58</number>
</figureCitation>
); paramere stout and triangularly curved upwards, lateral part with distinctly angular projection, apex narrowed and blunt (
<figureCitation box="[880,973,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[985,1016,1879,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">83</figureCitation>
). Endosoma (
<figureCitation box="[1169,1262,1878,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 67 – 71" captionStartId="8.[151,264,774,796]" captionTargetBox="[215,1372,209,747]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[204,1384,193,752]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 67 – 71. Endosoma of Metrocoris spp. (males) in dorsal view. 67. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 68. M. astictus sp. nov.; 69. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 70. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 71. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269721/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Figs. 71</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1274,1348,1879,1903]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
81, 
<number box="[1316,1348,1879,1903]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="82.0">82</number>
</figureCitation>
): dorsal sclerite long and recurved proximally, apical accessory sclerites small, accessory lateral sclerites thick and straight, ventral sclerites present and long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,690,2011]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1437,151,896]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="373" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,394,1986,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">Apterous female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[409,491,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 29 – 33" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1570,1592]" captionTargetBox="[174,1408,781,1541]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[168,1419,777,1549]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 29 – 33. Photographs of bodies of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in dorsal view (females). 29. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 30. M. astictus sp. nov.; 31. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 32. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 33. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm. Figures. 34 – 38. Photographs of abdmen of apterous morph of Metrocoris spp. in ventral view (females). 34. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993; 35. M. astictus sp. nov.; 36. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 37. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 38. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 1.0 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269717/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="372">
Fig. 
<number box="[460,491,1987,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="33.0">33</number>
</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<number box="[655,770,1986,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="6.1" valueMax="6.13" valueMin="6.07">6.07–6.13</number>
, body width (across acetabula) 
<number box="[1120,1235,1986,2011]" pageId="13" pageNumber="372" value="3.38" valueMax="3.4" valueMin="3.36">3.36–3.40</number>
. Colour similar to apterous male. Structural characters: head length 
<number box="[724,839,152,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.715" valueMax="0.73" valueMin="0.7">0.70–0.73</number>
, head width 
<number box="[992,1107,151,176]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="1.59" valueMax="1.61" valueMin="1.57">1.57–1.61</number>
, minimum interocular width 
<number box="[151,267,188,213]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.635" valueMax="0.65" valueMin="0.62">0.62–0.65</number>
; antenna about 
<number box="[448,497,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.74">0.74</number>
times as long as body, lengths of antennal segments I–IV: 
<number box="[1183,1235,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="2.01">2.01</number>
, 
<number box="[1248,1300,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.89">0.89</number>
, 
<number box="[1314,1366,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.91">0.91</number>
, 
<number box="[1380,1432,188,212]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.74">0.74</number>
; pronotum slightly narrower than head, pronotum length 
<number box="[779,894,223,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.485" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.47">0.47–0.50</number>
, pronotum width 
<number box="[1091,1206,223,248]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="1.69" valueMax="1.71" valueMin="1.67">1.67–1.71</number>
; fore femora slender without teeth, ratio length/width 
<number box="[518,555,260,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="6.9">6.9</number>
, inner surface of fore tibiae not modified; lengths of leg segments (femur, tibia and tarsus): fore leg: 
<number box="[392,444,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="2.75">2.75</number>
, 
<number box="[456,505,296,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="2.31">2.31</number>
and 1.00 (
<number box="[625,677,296,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.12">0.12</number>
+ 
<number box="[693,744,296,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.88">0.88</number>
), middle leg: 
<number box="[900,952,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="6.81">6.81</number>
, 
<number box="[964,1013,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="5.39">5.39</number>
and 
<number box="[1069,1118,296,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="2.91">2.91</number>
(
<number box="[1134,1184,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="2.31">2.31</number>
+ 
<number box="[1200,1253,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.6">0.60</number>
), hind leg: 
<number box="[1380,1432,295,320]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="6.78">6.78</number>
, 
<number box="[151,200,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="4.5">4.50</number>
and 
<number box="[257,306,332,356]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.98">0.98</number>
(
<number box="[323,375,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.53">0.53</number>
+ 
<number box="[391,443,332,357]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="0.45">0.45</number>
). Female terminalia: abdominal sternum VII relatively large, about as long as length of preceding abdominal sterna together, laterally constricted, apical half forming a broad lobe, caudal margin without median notch, not completely covering apex of abdomen in ventral view (Fig. 
<number box="[1031,1062,404,428]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="38.0">38</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,896]" box="[199,869,439,464]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,750,439,464]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Macropterous female and macropterous male.</emphasis>
unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="373" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,476,501]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named in honour of Prof. Leyi Zheng for his outstanding contribution to the studies on 
<taxonomicName box="[151,287,512,535]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Heteroptera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="374" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Heteroptera</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="373" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,896]" box="[199,660,548,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,548,573]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,426,548,573]" name="China" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">China</collectingCountry>
(Guizhou) (
<figureCitation box="[563,648,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 84" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1006,1028]" captionTargetBox="[158,1426,202,978]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,193,984]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 84. Geographical distribution of Metrocoris spp. in this study." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269723/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
Fig. 
<number box="[616,648,548,572]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="84.0">84</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,896]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,426,583,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Comparative notes</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[443,554,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[443,554,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">M. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[563,653,583,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[563,653,583,608]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
fits the diagnostic characters of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1068,1202,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lituratus">
<emphasis box="[1068,1202,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">M. lituratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" box="[151,408,620,645]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19, 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chen &amp; Nieser (
<number box="[338,399,620,644]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="1993.0">1993</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. The general appearance of this new species is also similar to the 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993" authorityName="Chen &amp; Nieser" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1157,1339,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">M. sichuanensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Chen" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" refString="Chen, P. P. &amp; Nieser, N. (1993) A taxonomic revision of the Oriental water strider genus Metrocoris Mayr (Hemiptera, Gerridae). Part I &amp; II. Steenstrupia, 19, 1 - 43, 45 - 82." type="journal article" year="1993">
Chen &amp; Nieser, 
<number box="[237,296,656,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" value="1993.0">1993</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the distinctive paramere blade of 
<taxonomicName box="[798,909,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zhengi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[798,909,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">M. zhengi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[916,1007,655,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,1007,655,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
is rather stout and triangularly curved upwards, and the lateral part bears a distinctly angular projection, with the blade apex narrowed (
<figureCitation box="[1281,1378,692,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 59 – 66" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1954,1976]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,1438,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[175,1411,1430,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 59 – 66. Paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males) in external view. 59 – 62. M. sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (59: Qingchen mountain; 60: Laojun mountain; 61: Xinmin village; 62: Hubaoxia Forest Park); 63. M. astictus sp. nov.; 64. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 65. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 66. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.2 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269720/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Figs. 66</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1392,1422,692,716]" captionStart="FIGURES 72 – 83" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1842,1864]" captionTargetBox="[209,1373,887,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[205,1381,876,1821]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 72 – 83. Illustrations of endosoma sclerites (dorsal and lateral views) and paramere of Metrocoris spp. (males). 72 – 74. M. astictus sp. nov.; 75 – 77. M. falciformis sp. nov.; 78 – 80. M. guizhouensis sp. nov.; 81 – 83. M. zhengi sp. nov.. Scale 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269722/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">83</figureCitation>
), while in 
<taxonomicName box="[249,429,728,752]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Metrocoris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="373" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[249,429,728,752]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">M. sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the paramere blade is relatively slender and straight, lacks an angular projection laterally, and has the blade apex slightly extended (
<figureCitation box="[614,692,764,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 5" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1240,1262]" captionTargetBox="[261,1319,180,1214]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[255,1332,171,1228]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 5. Photograph of Metrocoris sichuanensis Chen &amp; Nieser, 1993 (holotype, male) and illustration of diagnostic characters. 1. Habitus of holotype; 2. Related labels; 3. Male fore leg in lateral view; 4. Endosoma sclerites in dorsolateral view; 5. Paramere in external view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269713/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[704,734,764,788]" captionStart="FIGURES 6 – 12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,868,890]" captionTargetBox="[212,1367,193,840]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[212,1375,193,847]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 6 – 12. Photographs of Metrocoris bui Chen &amp; Zettel, 1999 (holotype, male) and illustration of diagnostic characters. 6 – 7. Habitus of holotype; 8. Related labels; 9. Male fore leg in lateral view; 10; Pygophore with proctiger and paramere in lateral view; 11. Endosoma sclerites in ventral view; 12. Endosoma sclerites in lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269714/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="373">10</figureCitation>
